content.description: Start in the chimney using the square block/ledge under the over hang. Move up and over the bulge using the left arete and some odd moves. Press onto the face and climb up to the top. Name is aptly suited.
content.location: Located on the same block as Toy Box, move around to the other side of the block where there is a slight over hang.

content.description: Sit start in the crack. get into position and power up to the top ledge. Use the big hands on top  of the block and big feet to top out.
content.location: To the right of One piece, about 10 feet. There is a large Crack cascading the whole length of the face from top to bottom.

content.description: Start middle of the block, with both hands on slopping ramp. move straight up the bock.
content.location: Climb the tall right most face on the One Up boulder The problem starts right above the large slanting foot ledge.

content.description: Sit start low.  Compression squeeze with both hands, find a key right heel hook and fire directly up the block. Finish on the large fin (Walk off is a traverse to the left).
content.protection: At least 2 pads and for sure a spotter! Top can feel very exposed.
content.location: One up is a large pillar/fin located in a pit to the right of cone head.

content.description: Low start on the detached boulder under the overhang. Power up to a good crimp in the middle of the face and fire to the top.
content.location: In the Hidie Hole area-- just right of power power, about 20 yards to the right.

content.description: Stand start with good feet and hands, power up to the large ledge in the middle of the face. From there move up feet and grab the top lip of the wall and top out. Tall but has good holds all they way up :)
content.protection: at least 2 pads and a spotter
content.location: The tall large wall to the right of Diamond in the Rough, farthest/ right most side of that wall is Dress Up. High Ball status achieved

content.description: Start as low as you can. Heel hook and use slopping holds to traverse the underside of the block. Move to the highest point of the block and mantle up and over to top out.
content.protection: at least 2 pads, and a but plate to be safe
content.location: Down about 5-7 feet  to the right of Weridy. Short power problem in the shape of a Dimond laying on its side.

content.description:
-Cone Head Left  

    -Cone head right

 Start on the slopping jugs on the corner and climb onto the left side of the face. from there use compression and some tiny feet to work your way up to the top. -There is a lesser variation that trends onto the right side of the face. Using the same starting holds at the left variation, make similar grade moves over the open ledge and use the pointed top to climb up and over.
content.protection: At least 2 pads and a spotter.
content.location: When walking up to the Summit Rock and Echo trail junction, you will run into a sign on a tree directing you ether right or left- ignore this and head straight, draping below the ridge line. Head down the gully for about 10 feet, then turn to your left. Cone head marks the beginning of the Hidie Hole area, Trend left under the ridge to find all climbing.

content.description: Spring/Fall preferable, Its ok in the summer. Most problems are VB too easy.
